  "body": "8951a03db39a2a877ada34c927d78352d465303e \n\nOSX & nix\n\nTry to restart geth post fork, geth ask to upgradedb\n\nRun upgradedb - in both platforms it imports all blocks by chunks of 2500, displays 'imported 444xxx blocks' (sorry can't remember exact num) and hangs the platform, completely (mouse frozen, etc, both nix and osx), - waited 2 hours just in case but nothing happened. \n\nReboot machine, restart geth, getting messages on osx about peer not being registered and on nix about being a 'bad peer'. \n\nSolution: wipe ./ethereum, reimport everything. \n",
